===Etymology===
Area etymon ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}). Compare {{cog|bo|ཕུང་པོ||heap}}, {{cog|bo|སྤུང||heap}}, {{cog|lep|a-pŭŋ||a heap; a stock}}, {{cog|lus||tr=puŋᴴ}}, {{m|lus||tr=punᴸ|t=increase; assemble}}, {{cog|lus|vûng|tr=vuuŋᴴ}}, {{m|lus|vûn|tr=vuunᴸ|t=swollen}}, {{cog|lus|vûng|tr=vuuŋᴿ||heap; mound}}, {{cog|cdm|भुङ्‌हसा|tr=bhuŋh-|t=to be burst or peak of activity (flowering, field work etc.)}}. Compare also {{cog|km|ពោង||protuberances/bumps on an animal's head}}, {{cog|km|សំពោង||puffed up; swollen}}.

{{och-l|邦|country}} may be the same etymon ({{zh-ref|Wang, 1982, Schuessler, 2007}}).

